HEADWORD: Fieldpiece
<hw>Field"piece`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A cannon mounted
on wheels, for the use of a marching army; a piece of field artillery;
-- called also <altname>field gun</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

